{{Infobox Election | election_name = San Marino general election, 1906 | country = San Marino | type = legislative | ongoing = no | previous_election = | previous_year = | turnout = '''86.3%''' | next_election = Sammarinese general election, 1909 | next_year = 1909 | next_mps = List of MPs elected in the Sammarinese general election, 1909 | elected_mps = [[List of MPs elected in the Sammarinese general election, 1906|Members elected]] | seats_for_election = All 60 seats to the [[Grand and General Council]] | election_date = June 10, 1906 | image1 = [[File:Green flag waving.svg|100x100px]] | party1 = Sammarinese Democrats | last_election1 = | seats1 = | seat_change1 = | popular_vote1 = | percentage1 = | swing1 = | image2 = [[File:Red flag waving.svg|100x100px]] | party2 = Sammarinese Socialist Party | last_election2 = | seats2 = | seat_change2 = | popular_vote2 = | percentage2 = | swing2 = | title = | posttitle = | before_election = | before_party = | after_election = | after_party = }} A '''general election''' was held in [[San Marino]] on 10 June 1906.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] & Stöver, P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p1678 ISBN 978-3-8329-5609-7</ref> It was the first-ever election in the country, after that the [[Sammarinese Citizenry Meeting, 1906|Citizenry Meeting]] had restored [[democracy]] three months before.
== Electoral law == The [[electoral law]] to select the '''1st term''' of the [[Grand and General Council]] was acted on May 5.<ref>[http://www.consigliograndeegenerale.sm/on-line/home/archivio-leggi-decreti-e-regolamenti.html?P0_path=%2Fhome%2Ftomcat%2Findicizzazione%2Findexleggi&P0_paginazione=15&P0_pagina=1&P0_orderBy=index_lucene%2Cdata_ordered%2Cnumero&P0_order=asc%2Cdesc%2Cdesc&P0_operatorMustBe=yes&P0_title=&P0_tipo=&P0_numero=&P0_anno=1906&annoiniziale=&annofinale=&P0_data_gg=&P0_data_mm=&P0_data_aa=&P0_document=&P0_data_ordered=&indicericerca=-1&x=20&y=13 Grand and General Council database. (it.) ]</ref> All [[householder]]s and [[graduate]]s over 25 years of age could vote. The republic was divided in nine multi-member constituencies according their population: *[[City of San Marino]] 22 seats, *[[Serravalle]] 12 seats, *[[Faetano]] 6 seats, *[[Montegiardino]] 4 seats, *[[Chiesanuova]] 4 seats, *[[Acquaviva]] 4 seats, *[[Domagnano]] 4 seats, *[[Fiorentino]] 2 seats, *[[San Giovanni]] 2 seats. All councillors were elected in their constituency using a [[plurality-at-large voting]], a [[non-partisan]] system. However, candidates elected belonged to the [[Liberalism|liberal]] group which had supported the democratic action of the [[Sammarinese Citizenry Meeting, 1906|Citizenry Meeting]] or, more, were members of the sole organized party of the country, the [[Sammarinese Socialist Party]], which claimed to have won 29 seats.<ref>[http://www.psd.sm/area/altri/enti/democratici/doc/doc100/nuovo_titano%20B%20.pdf Party of Socialist and Democrats of San Marino (it.) ]</ref> These two great factions formed together the first democratic government of the country.
